<br>
It would basically be there to keep the mob busy long enough for you to chain nuke the mob down.  It must have enough HP to live through a 30-second tier 1 (or PoS/PoV) fight and the aggro proc would keep the mob on it allowing the mage to nuke away with FoT, Black Steel, or whatever.   After fight is done, either make a new healthy pet, or let that one heal while you med (just like the old days).  Plus you'll have the 64 heal spell by then.<br>
<br>
I remember using DDD and chain casting Sirrocco and Char without getting aggro back at level 56.  It could be possible if balanced correctly.  By the time you get that level, have the upper level nukes and focus items, along with SCF-3 and other AA's, you really *should* have some chance to solo a mob still.<br>
