I am for doubling the hit points of our pets.  We traditionally have never 'hindered' the mob's ability to cause damage, and this solution is best in line with how 'things have always been.'<br>
<br>
If that idea is deemed not worthy, a proc slow would be great.  But if it is a summoned item, this would be a bad idea imo.  I have never seen where I had the time inbetween chain casting pets to hand the pet anything, so I would try to suggest that the proc does not come from an item we would summon, but rather as an innate ability of the pet.<br>
<br>
If the proc slow is a good idea, the fire pet still Hoovers due to low damage output and low hp.  If the proc came from the fire pet I think it would need to be about 175% slow for that gimp assed pet to stand a chance.  Make it on the earth pet please.<br>
