<br>
So that would be one answer, even with the weak upgrades we got in Kunark, a earth pet could still tank a mob in Skyfire and if you nuked without a resist you could win without chaining pets.<br>
<br>
It seems to me that one answer lies again in upping the hit points on pets so they can absorb damage long enough for us to nuke down the mobs. <br>
<br>
Sure it would be a close call, and no they won't stand a chance toe to toe with say a giant in PoS in the desert. However against the cactus for example they should have a chance.<br>
<br>
This is not stepping on the toes of melee because we have always done this. It is nothing new, and in an experience group with a melee, the pet is not hit.<br>
<br>
Would this mean a all pet group is desireable over a real &quot;tank&quot; per say. Yes if you have no cleric. A warrior without a cleric or some form of healer is not viable with a magician partner.<br>
<br>
2 mages were always better grouped than a mage/warrior, so that argumant is mute. Cleric Warrior is always viable, and do not forget a warrior can get a weapon that procs SLOW. I read in this thread how many are afraid a warrior would ask for slow if we got it. I think you should all know there are weapons that proc slow for rangers/warrior etc.. so yes they can slow. We can't, and we are a caster and they aren't.<br>
<br>
Sacred cows such as Root and Snare need to be examined as possibilites.<br>
<br>
Root for instance to make chaining a pet possible has a huge hidden cost. Mainly making weapons/muzzle/belt for the pet. Or you go without and cut the pets hit points and damage potential a lot, making those spell useless if you chain. So even root while powerful doesn't make the pet all powerful, but weakens it because you won't have time to equipe it. It does give you an escape spell, and a chance to chain pets, like we had in the past.<br>
<br>
Don't rule our snare and root Raz because you don't think we need it (and your not, but you always inteject your opposition.), personally I think upping the pets hit points so they have a chance if you add summoned plate, summoned belt, summon muzzle, and 2 weapons that they have a chance to live long enough to burndown a mob. Just like we always did. Close fight, but doable.<br>
