Rhion, unfortunately, class lines have been cut down and destroyed. I can outdo most wizards for quick damage at level 61. Druids ar enot the 'jack of all trades but masters of nothing', they're the masters of everything that they always wanted to be. Melee class definitions so far haven't been too blurred, but casters are gone. Shamans aren' the 'utility class of the gods', they're the 'haha i can solo @#%$ that you can't kill with a group' people. Mages are the 'masters of conjuration', perhaps, but beastlords are quickly taking over as the best pet soloers. We've got nuking power, but we have no skills to mitigate damage to allow us to do that.<br>
<br>
EVERY SINGLE OTHER CLASS has ability to mitigate damage. This ability is what binds PoP -- without damage mitigation you're toast, no matter how much damage you can do. Rhion, what do you propose? I can't always log on for four or five hours to get a group in PoV/PoS. Our ability to solo for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> viable experience </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is gone.<br>
<br>
I like being able to deal damage. As a 61 mage, however, there's no way for me to gain experience. A lot of mages don't see how bad a problem this is for 61/62 mages now, because when they were doing those levels EVERYONE was 61/62, therefore making getting a group easy and fast. Now with the 65 AA farmers, we're SOL.<br>
<br>
I hate to sound whiny, but something needs to change.<br>
<br>
The era of mitigation has begun.<br>
